### Site Information
Los Angles is located in Southern California. The cities elevation ranges from sea level (near Venice beach) to Mount Lukens which sits at about 5,100 ft. As a city it is a place of ethinic and racial diversity, which accounts for a lot of its finanicial inequality. They are considered to have a semiarid or medittarnean climate, meaning they have pretty warm weather but also have a photochemical smog since the 1940s.
